					<h2 class="heading--2">Code of Conduct</h2>
					<p class="paragraph--1">As part of our efforts to make QSC 2022 a successful and productive event, Qualys is committed to providing a safe, professional and welcoming environment for all participants. To that end, we require everyone to follow this Code of Conduct, which details behavior expectations for all QSC 2022 participants, and the consequences for non-compliance.   </p>
					<h3 class="heading--3">Behavior Requirements </h3>
					<p class="paragraph--1">All participants should contribute to creating an environment of mutual courtesy and respect in all their interactions with fellow attendees, including the live discussions, and will specifically refrain at all times from behavior that is:    </p>
					<ul>
						<li>Disruptive </li>
						<li>Disparaging </li>
						<li>Harassing </li>
						<li>Offensive </li>
						<li>Abusive </li>
						<li>Discriminatory </li>
						<li>Threatening </li>
						<li>Illegal </li>
					</ul>
					<p class="paragraph--1">Participants will not make derogatory comments to anyone, and in particular (but not limited to) about their gender, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, race, religion, ethnicity, age, veteran status or national origin.  </p>
					<p class="paragraph--1">These behavior requirements apply to all QSC 2022 activities, including one-on-one meetings, group chat sessions, conference presentations, private messages, and training courses.
If you witness or experience inappropriate behavior, please contact our Events Manager, Anna Moraleda with your concerns. Email her at <a href="mailto:amoraleda@qualys.com" class="inline-link">amoraleda@qualys.com</a>.
   </p>
					<p class="paragraph--1"><b>Qualys retains sole and final discretion for determining what’s unacceptable behavior, enforcing this Code of Conduct, and taking appropriate action, including removal from the event. </b> </p>
					<p class="paragraph--1">
Thank you for your cooperation and help in making QSC 2022 an enjoyable and fulfilling event, where we can all network and exchange knowledge and ideas with each other in a collegial, supportive environment.
</p>
